senses
  entry
    definition "(quantifier) used with either mass nouns or plural count nouns for indicating a complete or almost complete lack or zero quantity of"
    examples ("we have no bananas" "no eggs left and no money to buy any" "have you no decency?" "did it with no help" "I'll get you there in no time")
    id oewn-02276242-a
    partOfSpeech a
  entry
    definition "a radioactive transuranic element synthesized by bombarding curium with carbon ions; 7 isotopes are known"
    id oewn-14671900-n
    partOfSpeech n
    synonyms (nobelium "atomic number 102")
  entry
    definition "a negative"
    examples ("his no was loud and clear")
    id oewn-07219764-n
    partOfSpeech n
  entry
    definition "referring to the degree to which a certain quality is present"
    examples ("he was no heavier than a child")
    id oewn-00051219-r
    partOfSpeech r
    synonyms ("no more")
  entry
    definition "not in any degree or manner; not at all"
    examples ("he is no better today")
    id oewn-00024946-r
    partOfSpeech r
  entry
    definition "used to express refusal or denial or disagreement etc. or especially to emphasize a negative statement"
    examples ("no, you are wrong")
    id oewn-00024715-r
    partOfSpeech r
source "oewn:2024"
